post_text: Dallas City Elementary must perform a health screening for each person, staff and student, prior to entry to the school building or loading a school bus. post_text:
Parents have asked about a couple items that we request students bring for in-person instruction.
1. The "supply box" needs to be large enough to store your child's supplies including crayons, pencils, markers, calculators, scissors, glue, etc. That way, we can pick up the box and take it outside for classes held outdoors. See the photos for examples of a small pencil box and a "supply box" that can hold more.
2. The water bottle needs to be clear/see-through with a tight-fitting lid.
3. The beach towel is for outdoor classes so students do not have to sit directly on the grass. They can also use it to stretch out on when reading outdoors.
Great questions everyone! Keep 'em coming!

post_text:
Preschool Screening Information
The Dallas City Preschool Screening this spring was postponed in March. While we know that screenings must be held, we are not sure of all the details of when and how it will take place. Here is the most up to date information we have on preschool screening.

If your child is currently enrolled in PreK: Your child will automatically be enrolled in PreK this fall. They will not need to be screened again.

If your child was scheduled to be screened in March: We still have your contact information and you will be contacted as soon as we know when and how we can screen your child.

If you want your 3, 4, or 5-year old child to be screened for the 2020-2021 school year: Please call the school office at 217-852-3201 and leave a message containing your contact information. The deadline to call is June 8. As soon as we know how and when screening will take place, we will contact you.

It is very important that if you contact the school if you are interested in your child attending preschool in the 2020-2021 school year.

post_text:
Proud to be a Bulldog!
89 meals, breakfast and lunch, provided to students every day this week.
3 cafeteria workers & support staff purchasing and preparing meals.
3 office staff members ensuring each family was personally contacted by phone or in person.
3 custodians and maintenance staff members deep cleaning the entire building in 3 days.
2 bus drivers & support staff making home deliveries of food and class work.
20 teachers creating an entirely new instructional system in hours.
6 paraprofessionals helping prepare Chromebooks and materials for students.
3 full time staff members making sure our office stays open and supporting our school community
2 administrators making sure everyone is getting what they need and reminding us all to take care of ourselves and each other
Countless hours of worry about our students and community
#bulldogstrong
